se visit  http nscverifications org welcome to verification services  Current cadets and alumni may obtain enrollment degree verifications by visiting the Registrar s Office   303 Shell Hall  or by completing a Letter Request Form  Non Directory Verifications  If the requested verification requires non directory information  i e  credit hours  GPA  schedule information  etc  the request must be submitted by the cadet  include the specific information requested and authorized to release  and must contain the cadet s authorized signature  Virginia Department of Motor Vehicles  For verifications to the Virginia Department of Motor Vehicles  please check with your local Virginia Department of Motor Vehicles regarding what additional documentation is required to obtain a license or ID card  A college transcript may be required or recommended as an identifying document  Cadets wishing to request a copy of their transcript should reference VMI s transcript request policy  Note  Enrollment is verified only for the terms in which cadets are actually enrolled   Certifications will indicate  anticipated to return  for future terms if a verification needs to be sent prior to the start of term  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 